The state should supply Mwingi farmers with certified drought-resistant seeds ahead of the planting season, nominated MP Robert Mutemi has said.He spoke at Kyethani Primary School on Monday after distributing relief food to 3,000 families. Each family received 12kg of maize flour and 4kg of rice.The food was donated by the Nairobi-based Hindu Religious Service Centre.Mutemi said timely supply of the seeds will enable farmers plant in time.Mutemi, who is running for Mwingi West MP, said elected leaders should provide tangible solutions to food security so that Kenyans stop relying on relief food and donations during famine.